The paper discusses an integrated navigation system for an unmanned ground vehicle operating in an unknown cluttered environment, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The system uses sensory data to support time-critical mobility, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The paper also mentions maintaining the robot in a safe, goal-oriented state, which involves control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
